ople on the raid to Kedge Keep tonight. I didn't exactly loose my temper but I left near the end of the raid in a big tiff. I just want apologize. Both for  leaving you in a potential bind should you have  needed my services and as First Officer in One Fellowship it leaves a rather bad taste in my mouth to act this way. <br>
<br>
Montag runs the most perfect raids I have ever seen when I get the chance to participate and I don't want anyone to think different because of my behavior, plus, I want to go on the next one to Kedge, I have unfinished business there, Bwahahahha.<br>
<br>
Sorry, If you want to know what this is really all about, you'll have to wait for the raid report.<br>
<br>
Morromid<br>
One Fellowship<br>
First Officer<br>
&quot;Always My Pleasure&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=montagmccleaud>Montag McCleaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of Dragon Fodder</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#000080>(3/10/03 2:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=111.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Apology</span><hr size=1> Let me clear this up for those who were not there.  There was a slip up on my part during the end of the Kedge Raid.  When we were finally able to get the Corrupted Seahorse to drop (needed for druid epic piece) I was in a rush to get the only 2 druids there to roll on it before the Corpse poofed.<br>
<br>
I told our Druids to random for 1-100 for the drop.  They  rolled and One of them seemed to have won the roll by the slightest of margins.  I said my congrats to him and told him to loot the item.  Which he did on MY say so.  The split second that the drop was in the persons  hand I saw on the chat text people saying &quot;that was a misrroll&quot;.  I scroll back up to realize that while Morro had rolled 1-100 the Winner had rolled 1-200.  ACK!!<br>
<br>
My Profuse apologies to both Morromid and the Winner for this mix up.  I know for a fact that the Winner did not in any way Purposefully random the wrong number,  it was completely my fault for not making Certain that the correct numbers had been randomed.  As it was, all i paid attention to was the number that was rolled (which in this case was Under 100 for both)  and i told the &quot;Winner&quot; to collect his prize.  <br>
<br>
In the Future i will Have to remind myself to make sure that the drops are handled correctly, as some of them can be very important to people and Mix-ups like this can really cause trouble.  Once again My apologies,  and i will do my best to make sure this doesnt happen again.<br>
<br>
And Morromid I thank you for your post here.  Be assured that we will be going into Kedge again and that I will always be glad to see you on My raids.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Montag McCleaud<br>
